00:40:36.200 --> 00:40:38.150
When I test that,
that's not what I find.

00:40:38.150 --> 00:40:41.120
Basically, the earnings yield
outperforms the magic formula

00:40:41.120 --> 00:40:43.780
pretty consistently,
and pretty consistently

00:40:43.780 --> 00:40:45.940
over five and 10
year rolling periods.

00:40:45.940 --> 00:40:48.260
I think it's the better
metric for the reason

00:40:48.260 --> 00:40:51.190
that I've outlined here, that
return on invested capital,

00:40:51.190 --> 00:40:53.590
mean reversion, is a
very real phenomenon.

00:40:53.590 --> 00:40:55.390
And it's an easily
explained phenomenon.

00:40:55.390 --> 00:40:58.320
